$$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $${A^2} = A.A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right].\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {1 + 1} &amp; { - 1 - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1 - 1} &amp; {1 + 1}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>and $${A^3} = {A^2}.A = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right].\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {2 + 2} &amp; { - 2 - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2 - 2} &amp; {2 + 2}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>Now, <br><br>$${A^3} - 2{A^2} = \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right] - 2\left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right] + \left[ {\matrix{
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {4 - 4} &amp; { - 4 + 4}  \cr 
   { - 4 + 4} &amp; {4 - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>= a null matrix

We have, $$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 3} &amp; 4  \cr 
   3 &amp; { - 2} &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ and $$B = \left[ {\matrix{
   { - 1} &amp; { - 2} &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   6 &amp; {12} &amp; 6  \cr 
   5 &amp; {10} &amp; 5  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$AB = \left[ {\matrix{
   { - 1 + 6 - 5} &amp; { - 2 + 12 - 10} &amp; { - 1 + 6 - 5}  \cr 
   { - 2 - 18 + 20} &amp; { - 4 - 36 + 40} &amp; { - 2 - 18 + 20}  \cr 
   { - 3 - 12 + 15} &amp; { - 6 - 24 + 30} &amp; { - 3 - 12 + 15}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow AB = \left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>Hence, AB is null matrix.
